         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper, we investigate if the weight function $(1 - x^2)^{-1/2}R(x)$, where $R(x)$ is a rational function of order (1, 1), admits Chebyshev quadratures. Many positive examples are provided. In particular, we have proved that the answer is affirmative if $R(x) = 1 + bx, |b| &lt; 0.27846.\ldots$</p>
